    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our clear focal point, boasting a standout 75.89 efficiency score. His favorable matchup against Nelson, R is bolstered by a significant 14% boost from a dynamic platoon advantage, making him an elite start for both counting stats and the stolen base upside we prioritize. Similarly, **Colt Keith** (65.83) and **Caleb Durbin** (65.15) represent our most reliable anchors. **Caleb Durbin** is particularly compelling despite his number nine slotting; his 19% SP skill advantage and the favorable wind conditions neutralize the batting order penalty, creating a high-ceiling environment for him to exploit the opposing pitcher\u2019s slower delivery for stolen bases.\n\nWe have navigated a few complex decisions, most notably keeping **Chase Meidroth** on the bench. His 44.21 score hovered near our marginal threshold, but he was ultimately squeezed out by the sheer volume of high-scoring platoon opportunities presented to players like **Josh Smith** and **Junior Caminero**. While **Yordan Alvarez** (53.69) faces a tough challenge against Early (2.97 xERA), his elite xwOBA of 0.434 and favorable wind drift mandate his presence in the lineup despite the suboptimal platoon. We are monitoring **Gary Sanchez** and **Dillon Dingler** closely; **Gary Sanchez** holds a slight efficiency edge, but both are positioned to capitalize on moderate matchups. With **Christian Yelich** remaining on the IL and **Zac Veen** still working through the system in Albuquerque, we are leaning on our depth to survive the gauntlet against some mid-tier arms today.",
